---

An R markdown file is a file that combines text based elements with chunks of code, dividing
them into separate sections which can be compiled into on html document.

---

```{r setup, message = FALSE}

data(mtcars)

```
---

The mtcars data set is loaded, and the cyl is plotted against the mpg. 

---
```{r}

plot(mtcars$mpg, mtcars$cyl)

```
---

Overall, R markdown is a simple way to write a report with the code integrated into the text, allowing for more clear and easy to follow projects. I would say I prefer using R markdown files over regular reports, due to the increased visual clarity they provide, with minimal additional effort required.
